The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Saturday, March 01, 2003  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	East Bengal captain Anit Ghosh underwent operation on his injured right knee under the supervision of Dr Anant Joshi in a city nursing home Friday. The club authorities informed that though he will be off for at least six months, he will be signed for the forthcoming season as well. 				 																																																	 Tapan Memorial moved into the semi-finals of the CAB knock-out meet Friday beating Wari by 17 runs. Meanwhile, Taltala Institute were relegated to the second division of the CAB league, losing to City AC Thursday. 				 																																																	 Former national diving champion Kanti Dutta passed away Sunday. Dutta (55) died after a cardiac arrest and is survived by his wife and son.				 																																																	 Muslim Institute beat Wari AC 2-1 in a BHA group B match Friday. In another match, Behala SA held Barranagore SC goalless.				 																																																	SOCCER: National Football League  East Bengal vs Tollygunge Agragami (Salt Lake Stadium, 2:30 pm)				 																																																	HOCKEY: BHA league Group B  Calcutta Rangers vs Chotanagpur (EB); Calcutta Parsee vs Belgachia United (MB) Matches at 2:30 pm.
